Partition explanation

- sda:
	- main virtual disk
- sda1 /boot:
	- boot partition unencrypted
	- contains GRUB(bootloader), kernel(core of OS) and intramfs (initial RAM filesystem)
- sda 5
	- encrypted partition
	|
	|___LVMGroup
			- flexible volume managamednt
			- resizes logical vol. 
			|
			|___root
				- contains OS
			|
			|___swap
				- virtual mem when ram is full
			|
			|___home
				- sep user data from system
			|
			|___var/log
				- prevents logs from filling / and crashing system
			|
			|___tmp
				- temporary files created by apps
			|
			|___srv
				- service data ( web or appdata
				 
“I use an unencrypted /boot, then a LUKS-encrypted partition containing LVM.
Inside LVM, I split system, logs, user data, and temporary files into separate logical
volumes to improve security, stability, and maintainability.”

command list: 

lsblk
cryptsetup status sda5_crypt
lvdisplay
vgdisplay
